WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:29.500 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:34.560 align:middle line:10%
>> The year, 1934, and
America, deep in the throes

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:38.790 align:middle line:10%
of a crippling depression, is
captivated by an ugly custody

00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:41.910 align:middle line:10%
battle for poor, little rich
girl, Gloria Vanderbilt,

00:00:41.910 --> 00:00:44.640 align:middle line:10%
and her $5 million inheritance.

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:47.730 align:middle line:84%
In one corner, her high
living socialite mother.

00:00:47.730 --> 00:00:50.820 align:middle line:84%
In the other, her concerned
aunt Gertrude Whitney.

00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:53.400 align:middle line:84%
And in the middle,
jeered at by crowds,

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:56.580 align:middle line:84%
hounded by the press, a
lonely 10-year-old girl.

00:00:56.580 --> 00:00:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And while her aunt
Gertrude may have won,

00:00:58.860 --> 00:01:00.975 align:middle line:90%
Gloria was a little girl lost.

00:01:00.975 --> 00:01:04.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Gloria Vanderbilt, once storm
center of a sensational court

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:06.720 align:middle line:90%
battle, is going on 13 now.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:10.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Passing isolated adolescence
before escaping into an abusive

00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:14.370 align:middle line:90%
marriage at just 17 years old.

00:01:14.370 --> 00:01:18.210 align:middle line:84%
Gloria would marry two more
times, to conductor Leopold

00:01:18.210 --> 00:01:21.740 align:middle line:84%
Stokowski and
director Sidney Lumet,

00:01:21.740 --> 00:01:26.210 align:middle line:84%
before finding her true love,
screenwriter Wyatt Cooper.

00:01:26.210 --> 00:01:29.370 align:middle line:84%
With Cooper and sons,
Anderson and Carter,

00:01:29.370 --> 00:01:33.170 align:middle line:84%
she created the family she'd
spent a lifetime searching for.

00:01:33.170 --> 00:01:35.630 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
she enjoyed success

00:01:35.630 --> 00:01:37.790 align:middle line:90%
as a painter and a writer.

00:01:37.790 --> 00:01:40.520 align:middle line:84%
But Gloria's happiness
was short-lived.

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:44.780 align:middle line:10%
In 1978, she lost Wyatt after
a series of heart attacks.

00:01:44.780 --> 00:01:48.470 align:middle line:84%
In characteristic style, her
pain did not keep her down.

00:01:48.470 --> 00:01:50.960 align:middle line:84%
Gloria poured her
energies into what

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:55.695 align:middle line:84%
would become her most unlikely,
but wildly successful venture--

00:01:55.695 --> 00:01:56.495 align:middle line:90%
blue jeans.

00:01:56.495 --> 00:01:58.810 align:middle line:84%
>> These pants fit
you everywhere.

00:01:58.810 --> 00:02:02.960 align:middle line:84%
>> By the late '70s, Gloria's
trademark swan was in more

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:06.740 align:middle line:84%
American women's closets with
her jeans outselling every

00:02:06.740 --> 00:02:09.440 align:middle line:90%
other brand.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:13.160 align:middle line:84%
And then, once again,
the unthinkable.

00:02:13.160 --> 00:02:16.220 align:middle line:84%
In July 1988, with
Gloria watching,

00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:20.120 align:middle line:84%
her son Carter disoriented,
confused, crept out

00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:22.040 align:middle line:84%
on the ledge of their
penthouse balcony

00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:25.340 align:middle line:84%
and jumped 14
stories to his death.

00:02:25.340 --> 00:02:27.200 align:middle line:84%
This time, Gloria
dealt with her pain

00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:30.140 align:middle line:84%
by writing "A Mother's
Story," a tale of loss

00:02:30.140 --> 00:02:33.530 align:middle line:84%
focusing not just on Carter,
but the myriad losses

00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:35.480 align:middle line:90%
experienced just in living.

00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:39.050 align:middle line:84%
>> I never do anything or
approach anything without

00:02:39.050 --> 00:02:42.650 align:middle line:84%
believing it's going to
be absolutely successful.

00:02:42.650 --> 00:02:45.430 align:middle line:90%
I don't hesitate.

00:02:45.430 --> 00:02:49.260 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, the minute you do,
you'd end up doing nothing.

00:02:49.260 --> 00:02:53.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Conversely, its message
is hopeful, strong,

00:02:53.720 --> 00:02:55.410 align:middle line:90%
and pure Gloria.

00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:57.830 align:middle line:84%
No matter how terrible
the loss, no matter

00:02:57.830 --> 00:03:02.220 align:middle line:84%
how much you think you can't
go on, you can, you should,

00:03:02.220 --> 00:03:03.020 align:middle line:90%
you must.

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:07.820 align:middle line:84%
>> In your most remarkable
book, "A Mother's Story,"

00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:15.950 align:middle line:84%
you begin with the words, "Some
of us are born with a sense

00:03:15.950 --> 00:03:17.510 align:middle line:90%
of loss.

00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:20.000 align:middle line:90%
It's not something we acquire.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:23.150 align:middle line:84%
It is with us from
the very beginning.

00:03:23.150 --> 00:03:27.680 align:middle line:84%
And it pervades us for
the rest of our lives."

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:29.120 align:middle line:90%
I think that's true.

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.340 align:middle line:84%
Some of us are born
with a sense of loss.

00:03:31.340 --> 00:03:33.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it's true of me, yes.

00:03:33.410 --> 00:03:35.405 align:middle line:90%
>> What does it mean for you?

00:03:35.405 --> 00:03:36.655 align:middle line:90%
What does that loss feel like?

00:03:36.655 --> 00:03:42.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it really
comes from not having a father,

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:47.000 align:middle line:84%
and my mother, who was
very elusive and really

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.040 align:middle line:90%
wasn't there.

00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:57.710 align:middle line:10%
And therefore, you are forever
trying to replace it, find it.

00:03:57.710 --> 00:04:03.170 align:middle line:10%
And it's just an irrevocable--

00:04:03.170 --> 00:04:07.700 align:middle line:10%
loss is the thing that is
the most motivating thing

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:11.420 align:middle line:10%
in my life and always
has been, and trying

00:04:11.420 --> 00:04:15.230 align:middle line:10%
to replace that
loss, trying to find

00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:23.160 align:middle line:10%
something that will assuage it.

00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:26.390 align:middle line:10%
>> What were some of the ways
that you tried to fill that

00:04:26.390 --> 00:04:29.015 align:middle line:10%
hole?

00:04:29.015 --> 00:04:31.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I never, ever--

00:04:31.390 --> 00:04:38.060 align:middle line:84%
one of the qualities and
the traits that I hate more

00:04:38.060 --> 00:04:39.860 align:middle line:90%
than anything is self-pity.

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:42.740 align:middle line:90%
And I certainly never had that.

00:04:42.740 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And I don't respect
people that do.

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:55.790 align:middle line:84%
But I always felt that I
was trying to find something

00:04:55.790 --> 00:04:57.080 align:middle line:90%
that I didn't have.

00:04:57.080 --> 00:05:00.770 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
as one develops,

00:05:00.770 --> 00:05:05.630 align:middle line:84%
and if you live long enough,
you find that, in a sense,

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:09.950 align:middle line:84%
you become your own mother
and your own father.

00:05:09.950 --> 00:05:11.810 align:middle line:84%
But that takes a
long, long time.

00:05:11.810 --> 00:05:12.950 align:middle line:90%
>> It does.

00:05:12.950 --> 00:05:17.220 align:middle line:84%
>> That doesn't come
early or easily.

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:22.140 align:middle line:84%
But it certainly is the point
that I've really reached now.

00:05:22.140 --> 00:05:23.900 align:middle line:90%
I don't have that--

00:05:23.900 --> 00:05:31.970 align:middle line:84%
well, loss is the thing
that still is the thing that

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:37.310 align:middle line:84%
obsesses me most, and that I
think about most in my writing,

00:05:37.310 --> 00:05:39.740 align:middle line:84%
that I'm trying to
find in my work,

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:46.295 align:middle line:84%
I try to find in a love
affairs, one tries to find.

00:05:46.295 --> 00:05:50.150 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things you
wrote that resonated with me

00:05:50.150 --> 00:05:58.540 align:middle line:84%
for so long was with each
successive loss in your life,

00:05:58.540 --> 00:06:00.110 align:middle line:90%
it became more familiar.

00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:01.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:06:01.490 --> 00:06:03.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And it was almost
a relief, you said.

00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:05.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:06.610 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:06:06.610 --> 00:06:11.870 align:middle line:84%
I can deal with loss very
easily because I've been there

00:06:11.870 --> 00:06:13.760 align:middle line:90%
and I'm familiar with it.

00:06:13.760 --> 00:06:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And when it comes, it's almost
oh, yes, this is something

00:06:16.730 --> 00:06:21.470 align:middle line:84%
that I can really
handle and that I

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:26.150 align:middle line:84%
can function with because
I've been there before.

00:06:26.150 --> 00:06:28.380 align:middle line:84%
>> There's sort of a
fascination with it too.

00:06:28.380 --> 00:06:31.230 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like
when you're a child,

00:06:31.230 --> 00:06:33.050 align:middle line:90%
you fall and you skin your knee.

00:06:33.050 --> 00:06:35.610 align:middle line:84%
And your mother says,
don't touch the scab.

00:06:35.610 --> 00:06:40.450 align:middle line:84%
And you can't help it,
it's so fascinating to you.

00:06:40.450 --> 00:06:44.150 align:middle line:90%
>> I think that is true.

00:06:44.150 --> 00:06:46.910 align:middle line:84%
I was talking the other
day with my son Anderson

00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:52.730 align:middle line:84%
and we were talking
about two relationships

00:06:52.730 --> 00:06:54.220 align:middle line:90%
that I have in my life.

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:59.565 align:middle line:90%
And Anderson said, well, mom--

00:06:59.565 --> 00:07:03.800 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:07.520 align:middle line:84%
these are not the
names of the people--

00:07:07.520 --> 00:07:11.930 align:middle line:84%
why would you want
to be happy with John

00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:13.915 align:middle line:84%
when you can be
miserable with Bill?

00:07:13.915 --> 00:07:18.420 align:middle line:90%


00:07:18.420 --> 00:07:21.100 align:middle line:84%
So this is sort of
in the same genre

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:22.310 align:middle line:90%
for what we're talking about.

00:07:22.310 --> 00:07:25.595 align:middle line:90%
>> And what was your answer?

00:07:25.595 --> 00:07:29.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I thought
about it a lot.

00:07:29.270 --> 00:07:31.990 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, really,
what is it that I want?

00:07:31.990 --> 00:07:36.020 align:middle line:84%
Do I want that feeling
of being miserable which

00:07:36.020 --> 00:07:39.380 align:middle line:84%
is, of course, also a
feeling of loss and all that.

00:07:39.380 --> 00:07:43.280 align:middle line:90%
Or do I want to be happy?

00:07:43.280 --> 00:07:45.731 align:middle line:90%
Interesting question.

00:07:45.731 --> 00:07:49.430 align:middle line:84%
>> It is a fascinating
question, my new friend.

00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:52.400 align:middle line:84%
It is a fascinating
question because I

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:54.590 align:middle line:84%
think we do have a
tendency to do that.

00:07:54.590 --> 00:07:59.210 align:middle line:84%
There are people who go to
the familiarity of pain.

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>> My mother, who I'm
endlessly obsessed with,

00:08:02.630 --> 00:08:05.340 align:middle line:84%
and to this day I'm
obsessed with her,

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:07.970 align:middle line:84%
and she was the most
elusive, beautiful,

00:08:07.970 --> 00:08:11.840 align:middle line:84%
like a butterfly that I tried to
catch and I couldn't and I was

00:08:11.840 --> 00:08:12.740 align:middle line:90%
always chasing her.

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:17.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't it interesting, the
relationship between a mother

00:08:17.450 --> 00:08:20.810 align:middle line:84%
and a daughter, because
on so many levels,

00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:24.400 align:middle line:84%
they are who we
model ourselves--

00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:27.635 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's "My Mother/My
Self" is Nancy Friday.

00:08:27.635 --> 00:08:28.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Nancy Friday's book.

00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:29.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:32.659 align:middle line:84%
--because in some cases,
they represent everything

00:08:32.659 --> 00:08:36.350 align:middle line:84%
that we draw away from
that we don't want to be.

00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:38.970 align:middle line:84%
And in some cases,
they are everything.

00:08:38.970 --> 00:08:42.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I have friends
who have daughters

00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:47.210 align:middle line:84%
and their relationship, it's
so tempestuous and they go

00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:51.030 align:middle line:84%
through-- and I never really had
that because I really never had

00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:51.830 align:middle line:90%
my mother.

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:54.840 align:middle line:90%


00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:57.560 align:middle line:84%
The custody case
happened when I was nine.

00:08:57.560 --> 00:09:01.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I didn't see her
again for a long time.

00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:07.940 align:middle line:84%
So my role models were
really movie stars.

00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:11.570 align:middle line:90%
I was obsessed with the movies.

00:09:11.570 --> 00:09:15.116 align:middle line:84%
Katharine Hepburn was somebody
that was sort of a role model.

00:09:15.116 --> 00:09:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
oh, I wish she was

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:19.511 align:middle line:90%
my mother, that kind of thing.

00:09:19.511 --> 00:09:22.400 align:middle line:84%
>> You made headline
lines when you were what?

00:09:22.400 --> 00:09:25.180 align:middle line:84%
6, 7, 8 years old with
that custody battle?

00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:26.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:09:26.030 --> 00:09:32.450 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, there are pictures
of you where even then,

00:09:32.450 --> 00:09:34.310 align:middle line:90%
there's a sadness about you.

00:09:34.310 --> 00:09:36.757 align:middle line:84%
There's a sense of loss in
pictures of you as a little--

00:09:36.757 --> 00:09:37.557 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:09:37.557 --> 00:09:38.357 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:09:38.357 --> 00:09:40.260 align:middle line:90%
>> --little girl.

00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:41.740 align:middle line:90%
Were you aware of the loss then?

00:09:41.740 --> 00:09:44.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I was so
happy with my--

00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:48.650 align:middle line:84%
I had a wonderful nurse who was
really a mother image to me.

00:09:48.650 --> 00:09:51.860 align:middle line:84%
And then I was
separated from my nurse,

00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:57.080 align:middle line:84%
my nanny, which was
really, absolutely

00:09:57.080 --> 00:10:01.150 align:middle line:84%
was the worst thing that
had ever happened to me.

00:10:01.150 --> 00:10:04.820 align:middle line:90%
But until then, I was happy.

00:10:04.820 --> 00:10:08.150 align:middle line:84%
And I often think, in looking
back on my custody case,

00:10:08.150 --> 00:10:11.990 align:middle line:84%
if Mrs. Whitney,
my aunt Gertrude,

00:10:11.990 --> 00:10:14.080 align:middle line:84%
had only taken
the money that she

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:20.880 align:middle line:84%
spent on the lawyers
and various other things

00:10:20.880 --> 00:10:24.170 align:middle line:84%
and given it to my mother, who
would have been happy, I think,

00:10:24.170 --> 00:10:29.150 align:middle line:84%
to go to Europe and live,
and let me stay with my aunt

00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:30.866 align:middle line:84%
and had my nurse
stay on, and then

00:10:30.866 --> 00:10:32.240 align:middle line:84%
eventually, my
mother and I would

00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:33.620 align:middle line:90%
have gotten to know each other.

00:10:33.620 --> 00:10:35.995 align:middle line:84%
That would have really
been the solution to it.

00:10:35.995 --> 00:10:41.390 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a strange thing,
isn't it, how as time passes,

00:10:41.390 --> 00:10:44.390 align:middle line:84%
even though they're not around,
that's when we get to know

00:10:44.390 --> 00:10:45.525 align:middle line:90%
and understand our mothers?

00:10:45.525 --> 00:10:49.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh,well, well, my
relationship with my mother

00:10:49.610 --> 00:10:51.075 align:middle line:90%
keeps changing every day.

00:10:51.075 --> 00:10:51.875 align:middle line:90%
>> Today, even?

00:10:51.875 --> 00:10:53.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:54.090 align:middle line:90%
>> How is it changing?

00:10:54.090 --> 00:10:55.950 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think about
her all the time.

00:10:55.950 --> 00:10:58.850 align:middle line:10%
Well, I understand
her better, more.

00:10:58.850 --> 00:11:01.910 align:middle line:90%


00:11:01.910 --> 00:11:04.160 align:middle line:84%
I feel that way
about my grandmother.

00:11:04.160 --> 00:11:09.230 align:middle line:84%
I feel that way about
the nurse I had.

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:14.420 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that way
about Leopold Stokowski,

00:11:14.420 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:84%
who has died, and who
I was very much in love

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:21.150 align:middle line:84%
with and very close to
at one time in my life.

00:11:21.150 --> 00:11:24.050 align:middle line:90%
But my relationship with--

00:11:24.050 --> 00:11:26.060 align:middle line:90%
it keeps changing all the time.

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:28.940 align:middle line:84%
>> What is your relationship
with your mother today?

00:11:28.940 --> 00:11:30.080 align:middle line:90%
Is she someone you love?

00:11:30.080 --> 00:11:30.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:31.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Is she someone you forgive?

00:11:31.750 --> 00:11:39.218 align:middle line:84%
>> I would love to see her
and have her in my life.

00:11:39.218 --> 00:11:42.564 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:42.564 --> 00:11:47.822 align:middle line:90%


00:11:47.822 --> 00:11:51.450 align:middle line:84%
>> While Gloria Vanderbilt was
born into a family of wealth,

00:11:51.450 --> 00:11:56.730 align:middle line:84%
prestige, and power, her
life was never an easy road.

00:11:56.730 --> 00:12:00.090 align:middle line:90%
Informed at every turn by loss--

00:12:00.090 --> 00:12:07.330 align:middle line:84%
of her father, her mother,
her true love, her child.

00:12:07.330 --> 00:12:10.600 align:middle line:84%
Through it all, she did
hold onto one thing--

00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:15.506 align:middle line:84%
faith-- in herself
and in a higher power.

00:12:15.506 --> 00:12:20.870 align:middle line:84%
>> You must have an enormous
amount of faith in your life.

00:12:20.870 --> 00:12:21.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:12:21.860 --> 00:12:23.045 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:12:23.045 --> 00:12:26.510 align:middle line:10%
>> How would you define
your faith today?

00:12:26.510 --> 00:12:30.040 align:middle line:10%
I think we all have different
definitions of spirituality,

00:12:30.040 --> 00:12:33.620 align:middle line:10%
of the road we walk down
that centers us, focuses

00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:37.650 align:middle line:10%
us, and allows us to have
an essential conversation

00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:38.450 align:middle line:10%
with God.

00:12:38.450 --> 00:12:38.855 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:12:38.855 --> 00:12:38.990 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:12:38.990 --> 00:12:40.985 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you define
your faith today?

00:12:40.985 --> 00:12:43.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I'm very fatalistic.

00:12:43.580 --> 00:12:47.570 align:middle line:10%
And I believe that
everything is preset.

00:12:47.570 --> 00:12:50.990 align:middle line:84%
And if you believe
that, it frees you,

00:12:50.990 --> 00:12:54.440 align:middle line:84%
because it's going
to happen the way

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:59.250 align:middle line:84%
it happens, and it's not going
to happen in any other way.

00:12:59.250 --> 00:13:04.890 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
that gives me great--

00:13:04.890 --> 00:13:08.390 align:middle line:84%
I also don't believe that
this is the real life,

00:13:08.390 --> 00:13:16.710 align:middle line:84%
and that this is just the
transition to something which

00:13:16.710 --> 00:13:19.170 align:middle line:90%
is going to be much better.

00:13:19.170 --> 00:13:20.510 align:middle line:90%
>> I love that.

00:13:20.510 --> 00:13:21.310 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:13:21.310 --> 00:13:23.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Much, much better.

00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:26.355 align:middle line:84%
And don't ask me how I
know it, I just know it.

00:13:26.355 --> 00:13:27.155 align:middle line:90%
>> I won't.

00:13:27.155 --> 00:13:29.660 align:middle line:84%
I won't ask you, because
you know-- and I'll tell you

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:32.150 align:middle line:84%
why I won't ask
you, because I think

00:13:32.150 --> 00:13:34.380 align:middle line:84%
that's what faith
is, just knowing.

00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:35.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:13:35.310 --> 00:13:38.270 align:middle line:90%
>> It's just a knowingness.

00:13:38.270 --> 00:13:40.250 align:middle line:84%
So you believe things
are choreographed for us.

00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:41.575 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:13:41.575 --> 00:13:46.580 align:middle line:84%
>> You believe that there are
better things and a better

00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:47.750 align:middle line:90%
place coming.

00:13:47.750 --> 00:13:48.935 align:middle line:90%
Do you pray?

00:13:48.935 --> 00:13:51.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:51.690 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:90%
>> All the time?

00:13:53.660 --> 00:14:00.200 align:middle line:84%
>> I pray-- what I really pray
is I thank the divine mother

00:14:00.200 --> 00:14:08.660 align:middle line:84%
for what I have, and my health,
and that my children are OK,

00:14:08.660 --> 00:14:11.030 align:middle line:90%
and my friends.

00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:16.250 align:middle line:90%
And I don't ask for things.

00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:17.070 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:14:17.070 --> 00:14:20.585 align:middle line:90%
>> I just thank for what I have.

00:14:20.585 --> 00:14:25.970 align:middle line:84%
>> A very wise, holy person said
to me once that the best way

00:14:25.970 --> 00:14:31.200 align:middle line:84%
to pray is not in supplication,
asking for things,

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:32.000 align:middle line:90%
but in gratitude.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:32.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:32.800 --> 00:14:34.580 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's what I believe too.

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:35.780 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:14:35.780 --> 00:14:42.690 align:middle line:84%
>> If America has royalty,
people would say royalty--

00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:45.920 align:middle line:90%
Kennedys, the Vanderbilts.

00:14:45.920 --> 00:14:48.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that
embarrasses me very much.

00:14:48.300 --> 00:14:49.640 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sure it does.

00:14:49.640 --> 00:14:52.012 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know, that's--

00:14:52.012 --> 00:14:58.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it might, but
people would say that.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:01.670 align:middle line:84%
So I would ask you,
what does it feel

00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:05.780 align:middle line:84%
like to have that
kind of celebrity?

00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:07.340 align:middle line:90%
To be watched?

00:15:07.340 --> 00:15:09.260 align:middle line:90%
To be studied?

00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:12.420 align:middle line:90%
To be scrutinized all your life?

00:15:12.420 --> 00:15:13.685 align:middle line:90%
What does it feel like?

00:15:13.685 --> 00:15:16.700 align:middle line:84%
>> When the custody case
happened, and I was nine,

00:15:16.700 --> 00:15:19.290 align:middle line:84%
I got an enormous
amount of publicity.

00:15:19.290 --> 00:15:23.420 align:middle line:90%
And I decided--

00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:28.530 align:middle line:84%
I don't know whether I
articulated it as I do now--

00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:31.580 align:middle line:84%
but I just thought, I
don't want to read anything

00:15:31.580 --> 00:15:36.170 align:middle line:84%
about myself because I want
to make something of my life.

00:15:36.170 --> 00:15:40.140 align:middle line:84%
And I rarely do read
anything about myself.

00:15:40.140 --> 00:15:40.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:15:40.940 --> 00:15:42.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Really.

00:15:42.380 --> 00:15:44.270 align:middle line:90%
And I don't think of myself--

00:15:44.270 --> 00:15:48.180 align:middle line:90%


00:15:48.180 --> 00:15:50.840 align:middle line:84%
I don't read
reviews of my books.

00:15:50.840 --> 00:15:52.850 align:middle line:90%
I don't read interviews.

00:15:52.850 --> 00:15:55.580 align:middle line:90%


00:15:55.580 --> 00:16:00.230 align:middle line:84%
I may look at this
interview, I may not.

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:04.820 align:middle line:84%
No, because the
minute you do it--

00:16:04.820 --> 00:16:08.552 align:middle line:90%
I like to keep clear.

00:16:08.552 --> 00:16:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, then let
me ask you this,

00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:16.310 align:middle line:84%
do you believe that there is
a consciousness of celebrity?

00:16:16.310 --> 00:16:19.640 align:middle line:84%
And by that I mean,
a responsibility

00:16:19.640 --> 00:16:22.580 align:middle line:84%
that you have to
have, an awareness,

00:16:22.580 --> 00:16:24.420 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of
the things you do

00:16:24.420 --> 00:16:29.410 align:middle line:84%
are watched by people,
the direction you take.

00:16:29.410 --> 00:16:32.630 align:middle line:84%
And people take a
lot of direction

00:16:32.630 --> 00:16:35.990 align:middle line:84%
from what you do because
you are in the public eye.

00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:41.210 align:middle line:84%
How do you behave responsibly
because your name has never

00:16:41.210 --> 00:16:43.010 align:middle line:90%
been in the mud?

00:16:43.010 --> 00:16:45.170 align:middle line:84%
And you've been a
celebrity for a long time.

00:16:45.170 --> 00:16:50.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I don't again,
think really in those terms.

00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:54.260 align:middle line:84%
I just couldn't do what I do
any other way than the way

00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:56.000 align:middle line:84%
that I do it, and
the way I live.

00:16:56.000 --> 00:16:58.105 align:middle line:90%
And I don't think--

00:16:58.105 --> 00:17:00.770 align:middle line:90%


00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:04.080 align:middle line:84%
see, I don't see myself
as a celebrity if--

00:17:04.080 --> 00:17:04.880 align:middle line:90%
>> I see.

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:06.150 align:middle line:90%
>> --you want to use that word.

00:17:06.150 --> 00:17:06.950 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:17:06.950 --> 00:17:11.550 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that
getting that kind of publicity

00:17:11.550 --> 00:17:20.089 align:middle line:84%
as a child that is, I think,
difficult is that people do--

00:17:20.089 --> 00:17:22.520 align:middle line:90%
it casts a long shadow.

00:17:22.520 --> 00:17:27.170 align:middle line:90%
You hear that name, or that--

00:17:27.170 --> 00:17:30.620 align:middle line:84%
and there's a
preconceived sort of thing

00:17:30.620 --> 00:17:33.230 align:middle line:90%
that follows the person.

00:17:33.230 --> 00:17:39.320 align:middle line:84%
And it really takes your whole
life to become someone worthy

00:17:39.320 --> 00:17:46.590 align:middle line:84%
of self-respect as a person,
not with that shadow of--

00:17:46.590 --> 00:17:47.755 align:middle line:90%
around you.

00:17:47.755 --> 00:17:50.870 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a wonderful American
actor by the name of Robert

00:17:50.870 --> 00:17:52.280 align:middle line:90%
Loggia.

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And he was telling me a
story about years ago.

00:17:55.250 --> 00:18:00.980 align:middle line:84%
He said, you know, I
auditioned for a play,

00:18:00.980 --> 00:18:05.570 align:middle line:84%
