00:23:40.240 --> 00:23:44.840 align:middle line:84%
to merge with my mother, and
be her, and look like her,

00:23:44.840 --> 00:23:45.640 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:23:45.640 --> 00:23:48.445 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you feel beautiful?

00:23:48.445 --> 00:23:53.110 align:middle line:84%
>> I think what I have works
for me, I'll put it like that.

00:23:53.110 --> 00:23:54.550 align:middle line:90%
And I've always felt that.

00:23:54.550 --> 00:23:56.350 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it is I have, it works.

00:23:56.350 --> 00:24:02.450 align:middle line:90%


00:24:02.450 --> 00:24:05.040 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't want to look any
other way than the way I look,

00:24:05.040 --> 00:24:07.090 align:middle line:84%
not that I think it's
perfect, because I don't.

00:24:07.090 --> 00:24:10.280 align:middle line:90%
But whatever it is, it works.

00:24:10.280 --> 00:24:12.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Meditation.

00:24:12.760 --> 00:24:15.670 align:middle line:84%
That's a different
kind of thing that

00:24:15.670 --> 00:24:18.515 align:middle line:84%
contributes to beauty, because
there is a spiritual beauty as

00:24:18.515 --> 00:24:19.315 align:middle line:90%
well.

00:24:19.315 --> 00:24:20.115 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:24:20.115 --> 00:24:21.340 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a calming.

00:24:21.340 --> 00:24:23.020 align:middle line:90%
It's a centering.

00:24:23.020 --> 00:24:25.074 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:24:25.074 --> 00:24:26.490 align:middle line:84%
Do you have a
mantra in your life?

00:24:26.490 --> 00:24:27.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I have--

00:24:27.680 --> 00:24:28.480 align:middle line:90%
yes.

00:24:28.480 --> 00:24:34.300 align:middle line:84%
And my mantra really
is what I believe

00:24:34.300 --> 00:24:37.900 align:middle line:84%
it takes to be
successful in whatever

00:24:37.900 --> 00:24:40.270 align:middle line:90%
work you decide you want to do.

00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.010 align:middle line:90%
>> Can you say it for me?

00:24:42.010 --> 00:24:45.750 align:middle line:90%
>> It takes courage.

00:24:45.750 --> 00:24:49.600 align:middle line:90%
It takes believing in it.

00:24:49.600 --> 00:24:53.290 align:middle line:90%
It takes rising above it.

00:24:53.290 --> 00:24:56.550 align:middle line:90%
It takes work.

00:24:56.550 --> 00:25:00.405 align:middle line:84%
It takes me liking
you and you liking me.

00:25:00.405 --> 00:25:03.290 align:middle line:90%


00:25:03.290 --> 00:25:06.560 align:middle line:84%
It takes the dreaming
soul of the human race

00:25:06.560 --> 00:25:09.780 align:middle line:90%
that wants it to go right.

00:25:09.780 --> 00:25:12.520 align:middle line:90%
Let's never stop dreaming.

00:25:12.520 --> 00:25:14.930 align:middle line:90%
Think about it.

00:25:14.930 --> 00:25:18.460 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most important
things, I think, in all of that

00:25:18.460 --> 00:25:22.780 align:middle line:90%
is, it takes rising above it.

00:25:22.780 --> 00:25:25.600 align:middle line:84%
Because when you think
of all the things

00:25:25.600 --> 00:25:29.350 align:middle line:84%
you have to deal with when
you're in a working situation,

00:25:29.350 --> 00:25:34.450 align:middle line:84%
in any situation,
and to know what

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:39.340 align:middle line:84%
to let go, and not
let it hold you back,

00:25:39.340 --> 00:25:42.115 align:middle line:90%
and that takes courage.

00:25:42.115 --> 00:25:46.660 align:middle line:84%
>> And with that, let's talk
about Carter for a few minutes.

00:25:46.660 --> 00:25:48.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:25:48.300 --> 00:25:53.360 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you do
with all of the--

00:25:53.360 --> 00:25:55.120 align:middle line:90%
what if I had said this?

00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:56.980 align:middle line:90%
What if I had done that?

00:25:56.980 --> 00:25:58.570 align:middle line:90%
What if I had just been--

00:25:58.570 --> 00:26:02.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's the terrible
thing that you live with every

00:26:02.660 --> 00:26:03.910 align:middle line:90%
day.

00:26:03.910 --> 00:26:09.190 align:middle line:84%
And you just have to again, as I
believe that things are preset,

00:26:09.190 --> 00:26:12.130 align:middle line:84%
and that I think there's
a reason that it happened,

00:26:12.130 --> 00:26:16.300 align:middle line:84%
that anything happens, and that
we don't understand it yet,

00:26:16.300 --> 00:26:17.470 align:middle line:90%
but someday we will.

00:26:17.470 --> 00:26:18.900 align:middle line:90%
And I think it's positive.

00:26:18.900 --> 00:26:20.220 align:middle line:90%
I think it's OK.

00:26:20.220 --> 00:26:22.040 align:middle line:90%
I really do.

00:26:22.040 --> 00:26:26.510 align:middle line:90%
But that torment that one puts--

00:26:26.510 --> 00:26:28.720 align:middle line:90%
I know it well.

00:26:28.720 --> 00:26:30.055 align:middle line:90%
I know it well.

00:26:30.055 --> 00:26:31.240 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sure you do.

00:26:31.240 --> 00:26:37.060 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's very, very
difficult. And with time,

00:26:37.060 --> 00:26:39.770 align:middle line:84%
cliche though it is,
it does get better.

00:26:39.770 --> 00:26:43.370 align:middle line:84%
It'll be 12 years that
I lost Carter in July.

00:26:43.370 --> 00:26:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And in the beginning,
you think you're never

00:26:47.020 --> 00:26:52.680 align:middle line:84%
going to laugh again
or really live again.

00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:56.350 align:middle line:90%


00:26:56.350 --> 00:26:58.270 align:middle line:90%
But you do.

00:26:58.270 --> 00:27:03.010 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're saying that
you don't really recover,

00:27:03.010 --> 00:27:06.640 align:middle line:84%
but you laugh again,
you live again.

00:27:06.640 --> 00:27:09.970 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember the
first time you laughed--

00:27:09.970 --> 00:27:14.506 align:middle line:84%
felt something and
thought, I haven't laughed,

00:27:14.506 --> 00:27:18.130 align:middle line:90%
I haven't laughed in so long?

00:27:18.130 --> 00:27:21.548 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember coming
back into the world?

00:27:21.548 --> 00:27:25.312 align:middle line:84%
>> Slowly, but
very, very slowly.

00:27:25.312 --> 00:27:31.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Many people, when something
like this occurs in their life,

00:27:31.970 --> 00:27:33.980 align:middle line:84%
they think, I cannot
go to a support group.

00:27:33.980 --> 00:27:34.780 align:middle line:90%
I cannot--

00:27:34.780 --> 00:27:35.246 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:27:35.246 --> 00:27:36.046 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:27:36.046 --> 00:27:37.550 align:middle line:90%
>> --talk to another person.

00:27:37.550 --> 00:27:41.540 align:middle line:90%
No one will understand.

00:27:41.540 --> 00:27:43.340 align:middle line:84%
For the people
watching this broadcast

00:27:43.340 --> 00:27:48.800 align:middle line:84%
who are in that position
now, please talk to them.

00:27:48.800 --> 00:27:49.675 align:middle line:90%
What do you say?

00:27:49.675 --> 00:27:53.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think really,
it's such a personal thing.

00:27:53.300 --> 00:27:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And some people
cannot communicate.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:01.460 align:middle line:90%


00:28:01.460 --> 00:28:05.510 align:middle line:84%
They're very locked
into themselves

00:28:05.510 --> 00:28:08.060 align:middle line:84%
and can't break
out of themselves

00:28:08.060 --> 00:28:14.530 align:middle line:84%
and are afraid of showing
that terrible grief and pain.

00:28:14.530 --> 00:28:16.920 align:middle line:84%
But it really makes
such a difference.

00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:19.100 align:middle line:84%
And you feel this
incredible closeness

00:28:19.100 --> 00:28:22.400 align:middle line:84%
because you're with people
you don't have to explain,

00:28:22.400 --> 00:28:23.700 align:middle line:90%
you don't have to talk.

00:28:23.700 --> 00:28:27.200 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to even say
anything if you don't want to.

00:28:27.200 --> 00:28:30.140 align:middle line:84%
I have a friend and
she lost her son.

00:28:30.140 --> 00:28:33.440 align:middle line:84%
And she sometimes goes with
me to the support group,

00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:34.910 align:middle line:90%
and she never says anything.

00:28:34.910 --> 00:28:35.720 align:middle line:90%
She just listens.

00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:40.800 align:middle line:84%
But it helps her to
be able to do that.

00:28:40.800 --> 00:28:43.370 align:middle line:84%
But if you don't feel it,
if you don't want to do it,

00:28:43.370 --> 00:28:44.810 align:middle line:90%
you shouldn't do it.

00:28:44.810 --> 00:28:48.680 align:middle line:84%
Just give it a try, maybe
once, to see if it would work.

00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:51.050 align:middle line:84%
>> That's the best advice in
the world-- just go once--

00:28:51.050 --> 00:28:51.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Once.

00:28:51.710 --> 00:28:52.626 align:middle line:90%
>> --what can it hurt?

00:28:52.626 --> 00:28:55.010 align:middle line:84%
>> And also, you can go
and after five minutes,

00:28:55.010 --> 00:28:56.520 align:middle line:90%
you can just get up and leave.

00:28:56.520 --> 00:28:59.030 align:middle line:84%
There's no pressure
at a support group.

00:28:59.030 --> 00:29:04.730 align:middle line:84%
There's no feeling of, it's
going to be silly if I get up

00:29:04.730 --> 00:29:06.370 align:middle line:90%
and walk away.

00:29:06.370 --> 00:29:07.710 align:middle line:90%
It's not like that at all.

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:09.440 align:middle line:84%
You can just do
anything that you want.

00:29:09.440 --> 00:29:14.015 align:middle line:84%
>> Did you ever go through
a period of, it's my fault?

00:29:14.015 --> 00:29:14.870 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:29:14.870 --> 00:29:15.670 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:29:15.670 --> 00:29:16.500 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:29:16.500 --> 00:29:17.610 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:29:17.610 --> 00:29:18.410 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:29:18.410 --> 00:29:20.400 align:middle line:90%
>> That's so good.

00:29:20.400 --> 00:29:21.490 align:middle line:90%
I think so many people--

00:29:21.490 --> 00:29:22.290 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:29:22.290 --> 00:29:26.220 align:middle line:90%
No, that, I never did.

00:29:26.220 --> 00:29:33.060 align:middle line:84%
>> It must be of great comfort
to you to know that Carter knew

00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:36.465 align:middle line:90%
and was sure that he was loved.

00:29:36.465 --> 00:29:38.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:29:38.040 --> 00:29:40.540 align:middle line:90%
And I know he loved me too.

00:29:40.540 --> 00:29:45.500 align:middle line:90%
>> He fell 14 stories.

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:50.120 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, you write, you
stand outside a building

00:29:50.120 --> 00:29:54.330 align:middle line:90%
and you count 14 stories up.

00:29:54.330 --> 00:29:55.890 align:middle line:90%
Why do you do that?

00:29:55.890 --> 00:29:56.690 align:middle line:90%
Is it--

00:29:56.690 --> 00:30:00.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Because I think it's very
important to go over it again,

00:30:00.710 --> 00:30:02.760 align:middle line:90%
and again, and again, and again.

00:30:02.760 --> 00:30:13.200 align:middle line:84%
That's the only way that
you come to assuage pain.

00:30:13.200 --> 00:30:17.300 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
important to do that.

00:30:17.300 --> 00:30:21.741 align:middle line:84%
I know some people,
they want to forget it

00:30:21.741 --> 00:30:23.240 align:middle line:84%
and they don't want
to deal with it.

00:30:23.240 --> 00:30:28.140 align:middle line:84%
But that is not the way
I have chosen to do it.

00:30:28.140 --> 00:30:30.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I understand
exactly why you do it.

00:30:30.590 --> 00:30:35.430 align:middle line:84%
For me, it would be a way
of putting chaos into order.

00:30:35.430 --> 00:30:36.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:30:36.230 --> 00:30:39.020 align:middle line:84%
>> It would be a way of
wrapping my head around it.

00:30:39.020 --> 00:30:44.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I go over it a lot
again, and again, and again.

00:30:44.270 --> 00:30:49.760 align:middle line:84%
I even, like a movie,
play it backwards.

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:52.270 align:middle line:84%
I did that a lot, actually,
in the very beginning.

00:30:52.270 --> 00:30:57.570 align:middle line:90%


00:30:57.570 --> 00:31:02.217 align:middle line:84%
And then when it was happening--
because he didn't jump,

00:31:02.217 --> 00:31:03.300 align:middle line:90%
he was holding on to the--

00:31:03.300 --> 00:31:04.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Hanging onto the ledge.

00:31:04.770 --> 00:31:09.960 align:middle line:84%
>> --ledge, and for a minute,
I thought he was going to come

00:31:09.960 --> 00:31:12.060 align:middle line:90%
back again--

00:31:12.060 --> 00:31:18.560 align:middle line:90%
and as it was happening, I saw--

00:31:18.560 --> 00:31:21.630 align:middle line:84%
it was as if I went
up into the sky

00:31:21.630 --> 00:31:24.270 align:middle line:84%
and was looking
down on the balcony

00:31:24.270 --> 00:31:26.299 align:middle line:90%
with two people on the balcony.

00:31:26.299 --> 00:31:27.840 align:middle line:84%
And I've heard that,
actually, that's

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:29.610 align:middle line:84%
a rather common
thing when somebody's

00:31:29.610 --> 00:31:31.620 align:middle line:84%
in an accident or
something, you get a sort

00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:37.110 align:middle line:90%
of out of body experience.

00:31:37.110 --> 00:31:43.560 align:middle line:84%
But and I go over the
whole thing a lot.

00:31:43.560 --> 00:31:45.110 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
important to do it.

00:31:45.110 --> 00:31:50.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Is there a passage,
something you read,

00:31:50.310 --> 00:31:52.650 align:middle line:84%
something that
gives you comfort,

00:31:52.650 --> 00:31:54.990 align:middle line:84%
something that you read
over and over again?

00:31:54.990 --> 00:31:59.980 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, well, there's one
thing from Willa Cather's "My

00:31:59.980 --> 00:32:07.320 align:middle line:10%
ntonia," which, it actually,
it applies to what we're talking

00:32:07.320 --> 00:32:15.255 align:middle line:10%
about, but it's how I
imagine death to be.

00:32:15.255 --> 00:32:16.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'll read it
to you, shall I?

00:32:16.630 --> 00:32:20.406 align:middle line:84%
>> I would love for
you to read it to me.

00:32:20.406 --> 00:32:26.430 align:middle line:84%
>> "I kept as still as I
could, nothing happened.

00:32:26.430 --> 00:32:30.270 align:middle line:84%
I did not expect
anything to happen.

00:32:30.270 --> 00:32:34.830 align:middle line:84%
I was something that lay
under the sun and felt it,

00:32:34.830 --> 00:32:37.310 align:middle line:90%
like the pumpkin.

00:32:37.310 --> 00:32:40.560 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't not
want to be anymore.

00:32:40.560 --> 00:32:43.680 align:middle line:90%


00:32:43.680 --> 00:32:46.660 align:middle line:90%
I was entirely happy.

00:32:46.660 --> 00:32:50.250 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps we feel like that
when we die and become

00:32:50.250 --> 00:32:53.760 align:middle line:84%
part of something
entire, whether it

00:32:53.760 --> 00:32:59.550 align:middle line:84%
is sun and air, or
goodness and knowledge.

00:32:59.550 --> 00:33:05.820 align:middle line:84%
At any rate, that is happiness,
to be dissolved into something

00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:09.060 align:middle line:90%
complete and great.

00:33:09.060 --> 00:33:13.620 align:middle line:84%
When it comes to one, it
comes as naturally as sleep."

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:16.980 align:middle line:90%


00:33:16.980 --> 00:33:20.340 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:33:20.340 --> 00:33:24.660 align:middle line:90%


00:33:24.660 --> 00:33:28.025 align:middle line:84%
>> Gloria Vanderbilt did
not know love as a child.

00:33:28.025 --> 00:33:30.320 align:middle line:84%
Her father died when
she was an infant.

00:33:30.320 --> 00:33:33.080 align:middle line:84%
>> The famous Mrs. Gloria
Vanderbilt arrives in her

00:33:33.080 --> 00:33:34.620 align:middle line:90%
chariot as the sun goddess.

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Her globetrotting mother
cared more for parties

00:33:37.490 --> 00:33:41.060 align:middle line:84%
and left her in the company
of a cold and aloof aunt

00:33:41.060 --> 00:33:43.740 align:middle line:90%
who became her legal guardian.

00:33:43.740 --> 00:33:48.000 align:middle line:84%
But Gloria has known love as
an adult, and plenty of it--

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:52.200 align:middle line:84%
romances with Howard
Hughes and Frank Sinatra,

00:33:52.200 --> 00:33:55.980 align:middle line:84%
marriages to charismatic
conductor Leopold Stokowski,

00:33:55.980 --> 00:34:00.420 align:middle line:84%
40 years her senior,
director Sidney Lumet,

00:34:00.420 --> 00:34:02.790 align:middle line:84%
who she met while acting
in the New York stage

00:34:02.790 --> 00:34:04.890 align:middle line:90%
version of "Picnic."

00:34:04.890 --> 00:34:07.860 align:middle line:84%
And finally, when
she was in her 40s,

00:34:07.860 --> 00:34:13.335 align:middle line:84%
screenwriter Wyatt Cooper,
who she calls her great love.

00:34:13.335 --> 00:34:16.780 align:middle line:10%
>> You have been in your life,
as I read all of your books,

00:34:16.780 --> 00:34:19.350 align:middle line:10%
and as I've followed your
life for quite some time,

00:34:19.350 --> 00:34:22.640 align:middle line:10%
you have been with some of
the most remarkable men.

00:34:22.640 --> 00:34:23.440 align:middle line:10%
Wyatt Cooper.

00:34:23.440 --> 00:34:27.504 align:middle line:10%
>> What amazing
parent he was, Wyatt.

00:34:27.504 --> 00:34:29.055 align:middle line:10%
>> Was he a wonderful father?

00:34:29.055 --> 00:34:32.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, certainly.

00:34:32.340 --> 00:34:35.010 align:middle line:84%
Showed me what it would
be like to have a father,

00:34:35.010 --> 00:34:38.100 align:middle line:84%
the way he was with
Carter and Anderson.

00:34:38.100 --> 00:34:41.460 align:middle line:84%
>> How wonderful that you
married a man who's a wonderful

00:34:41.460 --> 00:34:43.590 align:middle line:90%
father when your father was not.

00:34:43.590 --> 00:34:45.497 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:34:45.497 --> 00:34:50.040 align:middle line:84%
>> And you know, he and
Carter were so close.

00:34:50.040 --> 00:34:59.370 align:middle line:84%
And after Carter died,
I thought it was as if--

00:34:59.370 --> 00:35:00.810 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how to explain it--

00:35:00.810 --> 00:35:04.020 align:middle line:84%
but I was so happy
that, if it had

00:35:04.020 --> 00:35:08.220 align:middle line:84%
to be that it was me there
instead of him, because he

00:35:08.220 --> 00:35:09.420 align:middle line:90%
couldn't have survived it.

00:35:09.420 --> 00:35:10.605 align:middle line:90%
He couldn't have.

00:35:10.605 --> 00:35:12.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Sidney Lumet?

00:35:12.000 --> 00:35:13.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, Sydney's wonderful, yes.

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:19.920 align:middle line:84%
The warmest, most passionate,
generous, spirited, person.

00:35:19.920 --> 00:35:21.680 align:middle line:90%
I love him dearly.

00:35:21.680 --> 00:35:25.870 align:middle line:90%
>> Remarkable man, Sidney.

00:35:25.870 --> 00:35:27.175 align:middle line:90%
>> Leopold?

00:35:27.175 --> 00:35:30.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, he was a
genius, is a genius.

00:35:30.340 --> 00:35:34.240 align:middle line:84%
And geniuses are not
easy to live with.

00:35:34.240 --> 00:35:36.395 align:middle line:90%
>> I imagine he was not.

00:35:36.395 --> 00:35:40.015 align:middle line:84%
>> But I was just
crazy about him.

00:35:40.015 --> 00:35:47.410 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, they say that there
is a common thread in the men

00:35:47.410 --> 00:35:49.210 align:middle line:90%
we love.

00:35:49.210 --> 00:35:51.980 align:middle line:84%
Even though their personalities
may be very different,

00:35:51.980 --> 00:35:54.430 align:middle line:84%
there's a common
denominator, aside from you,

00:35:54.430 --> 00:35:56.170 align:middle line:90%
of course, that they have.

00:35:56.170 --> 00:35:58.330 align:middle line:84%
What was a quality,
do you think,

00:35:58.330 --> 00:36:01.495 align:middle line:84%
that all the men
you've loved have had?

00:36:01.495 --> 00:36:03.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they were
all so different.

00:36:03.650 --> 00:36:10.280 align:middle line:90%


00:36:10.280 --> 00:36:11.130 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:36:11.130 --> 00:36:16.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I can't find it, except
that they loved me a lot, which

00:36:16.550 --> 00:36:17.960 align:middle line:90%
is a thread, I guess.

00:36:17.960 --> 00:36:19.820 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a lovely thread.

00:36:19.820 --> 00:36:21.590 align:middle line:84%
Someone once said,
it's very important

00:36:21.590 --> 00:36:24.805 align:middle line:84%
to have a man love you a little
bit more than you love him.

00:36:24.805 --> 00:36:26.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I don't
think that's true.

00:36:26.180 --> 00:36:28.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you think that's true?

00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:31.160 align:middle line:84%
>> I think all love,
even if it's unrequited,

00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:34.430 align:middle line:90%
even if it's all--

00:36:34.430 --> 00:36:36.770 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't miss
it for the world.

00:36:36.770 --> 00:36:42.830 align:middle line:84%
>> When you write about Wyatt,
you say he was the one true

00:36:42.830 --> 00:36:44.960 align:middle line:90%
real love.

00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:48.410 align:middle line:84%
How do you know when
love is the real love?

00:36:48.410 --> 00:36:50.080 align:middle line:90%
What does it feel like?

00:36:50.080 --> 00:36:55.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, of course, you
do think that every love,

00:36:55.580 --> 00:36:59.630 align:middle line:84%
or you hope every
love, is the real love.

00:36:59.630 --> 00:37:06.945 align:middle line:84%
So and you can't know until
you've met the other love.

00:37:06.945 --> 00:37:07.820 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean.

00:37:07.820 --> 00:37:08.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:37:08.490 --> 00:37:08.830 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:08.830 --> 00:37:09.630 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:09.630 --> 00:37:10.840 align:middle line:90%
At the time, he's the one.

00:37:10.840 --> 00:37:11.550 align:middle line:90%
>> At the time, he's the one.

00:37:11.550 --> 00:37:12.350 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:12.350 --> 00:37:14.476 align:middle line:84%
>> He may not be Mr. Right,
but he's Mr. Right now.

00:37:14.476 --> 00:37:15.275 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:37:15.275 --> 00:37:16.400 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:16.400 --> 00:37:24.590 align:middle line:84%
But my marriage to Wyatt was
the most steady and real.

00:37:24.590 --> 00:37:29.825 align:middle line:84%
And I would be married to
him today if he hadn't died.

00:37:29.825 --> 00:37:32.690 align:middle line:84%
>> The other day I was with
a group of girlfriends and we

00:37:32.690 --> 00:37:35.300 align:middle line:84%
were talking about
when we date men,

00:37:35.300 --> 00:37:38.180 align:middle line:84%
there are certain
non-negotiables we have.

00:37:38.180 --> 00:37:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And by non-negotiables, we
mean there's just a few things

00:37:41.120 --> 00:37:43.190 align:middle line:90%
that there's no arguing about.

00:37:43.190 --> 00:37:48.410 align:middle line:84%
For me is, you can't smoke
and you've got to love dogs.

00:37:48.410 --> 00:37:51.230 align:middle line:84%
Those are the two
non-negotiables for me.

00:37:51.230 --> 00:37:53.510 align:middle line:84%
What would be
non-negotiables for you?

00:37:53.510 --> 00:37:56.846 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, smoking would
certainly be one.

00:37:56.846 --> 00:37:58.220 align:middle line:84%
>> What about a
man who's stingy?

00:37:58.220 --> 00:38:00.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, stinginess
I cannot hate--

00:38:00.500 --> 00:38:02.667 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I really hate it.

00:38:02.667 --> 00:38:04.250 align:middle line:84%
And it has nothing
to do with somebody

00:38:04.250 --> 00:38:07.980 align:middle line:90%
whether they have money or not.

00:38:07.980 --> 00:38:11.630 align:middle line:84%
It's a certain
generosity of spirit.

00:38:11.630 --> 00:38:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot of men
who do have a lot of money

00:38:14.750 --> 00:38:15.710 align:middle line:90%
are very stingy.

00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:18.040 align:middle line:90%
And I can't stand it.

00:38:18.040 --> 00:38:20.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's talk about a
very important topic.

00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:22.820 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about friendships.

00:38:22.820 --> 00:38:27.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I have the most
intense friendships with--

00:38:27.880 --> 00:38:29.960 align:middle line:90%
I have about 10 women friends.

00:38:29.960 --> 00:38:34.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so blessed
because I trust them.

00:38:34.880 --> 00:38:36.650 align:middle line:90%
They trust me.

00:38:36.650 --> 00:38:39.000 align:middle line:84%
I'd do anything in
the world for them.

00:38:39.000 --> 00:38:41.180 align:middle line:90%
And I know they would for me.

00:38:41.180 --> 00:38:45.440 align:middle line:84%
I trust women much more
than I do men, which I think

00:38:45.440 --> 00:38:50.180 align:middle line:84%
is probably because I was
brought up by women, really.

00:38:50.180 --> 00:38:52.850 align:middle line:90%
And I haven't a clue about men.

00:38:52.850 --> 00:38:54.260 align:middle line:90%
I really don't.

00:38:54.260 --> 00:38:56.450 align:middle line:90%
I haven't a clue.

00:38:56.450 --> 00:39:01.790 align:middle line:84%
And I have four boys, was
meant to have daughters.

00:39:01.790 --> 00:39:03.950 align:middle line:90%
But anyway, it's worked out OK.

00:39:03.950 --> 00:39:06.265 align:middle line:90%
But I haven't got a clue.

00:39:06.265 --> 00:39:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>> I wonder if we'll ever
really understand men?

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:12.790 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think they probably
are as sensitive as we are,

00:39:12.790 --> 00:39:15.320 align:middle line:90%
only I don't know, I find it--

00:39:15.320 --> 00:39:18.340 align:middle line:90%


00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:19.830 align:middle line:90%
it's another territory.

00:39:19.830 --> 00:39:21.210 align:middle line:90%
It's another country, you know?

00:39:21.210 --> 00:39:22.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it is.

00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:25.665 align:middle line:84%
I've always believed
men are another tribe.

00:39:25.665 --> 00:39:26.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:39:26.730 --> 00:39:28.125 align:middle line:90%
>> They are another tribe.

00:39:28.125 --> 00:39:30.250 align:middle line:84%
>> But they feel that
way about us, so--

00:39:30.250 --> 00:39:31.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:39:31.050 --> 00:39:33.600 align:middle line:90%
And they're entitled.

00:39:33.600 --> 00:39:35.730 align:middle line:90%
I have a bold question.

00:39:35.730 --> 00:39:39.260 align:middle line:84%
There was a time when you were
friends with Truman Capote.

00:39:39.260 --> 00:39:40.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:39:40.060 --> 00:39:44.050 align:middle line:84%
>> People have said over the
years that he was a mean man.

00:39:44.050 --> 00:39:44.850 align:middle line:90%
Was he-- would you?

00:39:44.850 --> 00:39:49.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Truman, what happened
to Truman in the beginning,

00:39:49.560 --> 00:39:53.190 align:middle line:84%
I knew him when we
were both like 18.

00:39:53.190 --> 00:39:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And what happened to Truman
is he got into the drugs.

00:39:56.820 --> 00:39:58.810 align:middle line:90%
And that's what did it to him.

00:39:58.810 --> 00:40:02.380 align:middle line:90%
He was a drug addict, got to be.

00:40:02.380 --> 00:40:04.560 align:middle line:90%
And then he completely changed.

00:40:04.560 --> 00:40:06.540 align:middle line:90%
And I think he was mean.

00:40:06.540 --> 00:40:11.700 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't see him at all
in the last years of his life

00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:15.670 align:middle line:90%
because he was--

00:40:15.670 --> 00:40:17.100 align:middle line:90%
well, I didn't trust him.

00:40:17.100 --> 00:40:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And I just think he did
really betrayed, really,

00:40:20.910 --> 00:40:23.130 align:middle line:84%
his real friends
like Babe Paley and--

00:40:23.130 --> 00:40:23.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Slim Keith.

00:40:23.930 --> 00:40:25.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Slim Keith, yeah.

00:40:25.300 --> 00:40:27.600 align:middle line:84%
>> You came out
of that unscathed,

00:40:27.600 --> 00:40:30.480 align:middle line:84%
as I read about
that over the years.

00:40:30.480 --> 00:40:32.940 align:middle line:84%
And I wondered if it was just
that you were wise enough

00:40:32.940 --> 00:40:33.740 align:middle line:90%
to step away.

00:40:33.740 --> 00:40:36.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, well, I never, ever--

00:40:36.060 --> 00:40:40.380 align:middle line:84%
I never confided him in anything
that I wouldn't want everybody

00:40:40.380 --> 00:40:45.750 align:middle line:84%
to know about, because he
was a brilliant gossip.

00:40:45.750 --> 00:40:52.770 align:middle line:84%
And he also, he said
to me once, if you

00:40:52.770 --> 00:40:56.710 align:middle line:84%
want to repeat something,
gossip about somebody,

00:40:56.710 --> 00:40:59.580 align:middle line:84%
he said, and you
want to make it up.

00:40:59.580 --> 00:41:05.280 align:middle line:84%
You have to take just a little
grain of truth about the person

00:41:05.280 --> 00:41:07.360 align:middle line:84%
so that when you
tell the rest of it,

00:41:07.360 --> 00:41:08.740 align:middle line:90%
they're going to believe it.

00:41:08.740 --> 00:41:11.580 align:middle line:84%
That was the way
his mind worked.

00:41:11.580 --> 00:41:17.430 align:middle line:90%
And I never, ever trusted him.

00:41:17.430 --> 00:41:21.360 align:middle line:84%
He was a wonderful companion
and great fun to be with,

00:41:21.360 --> 00:41:28.010 align:middle line:90%
but not to confide in.

00:41:28.010 --> 00:41:30.750 align:middle line:84%
>> What made you wake
up one morning and say,

00:41:30.750 --> 00:41:32.980 align:middle line:90%
I think I'll do jeans?

00:41:32.980 --> 00:41:35.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that was when
I was in the design--

00:41:35.730 --> 00:41:39.600 align:middle line:84%
and I started out in home
furnishings, designing.

00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:42.150 align:middle line:84%
The first fashion thing
I did was scarves, which

00:41:42.150 --> 00:41:44.070 align:middle line:90%
were done for my paintings.

00:41:44.070 --> 00:41:46.140 align:middle line:84%
And from that, I went
into my own business

00:41:46.140 --> 00:41:49.190 align:middle line:84%
on 7th Avenue, a
couture business.

00:41:49.190 --> 00:41:54.630 align:middle line:84%
And from that, one of
my licenses was jeans.

00:41:54.630 --> 00:41:56.370 align:middle line:90%
It really took off, very big.

00:41:56.370 --> 00:41:57.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you miss that world?

00:41:57.660 --> 00:41:59.880 align:middle line:90%
>> No, not at all.

00:41:59.880 --> 00:42:05.380 align:middle line:84%
No, I'm out of the business
completely, happily, yes.

00:42:05.380 --> 00:42:07.500 align:middle line:90%
No, I really don't.

00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:10.870 align:middle line:90%


00:42:10.870 --> 00:42:13.780 align:middle line:84%
The best thing about
it was making a lot

00:42:13.780 --> 00:42:15.520 align:middle line:90%
of money, which is always nice.

00:42:15.520 --> 00:42:19.840 align:middle line:84%
But when you're
in that business,

00:42:19.840 --> 00:42:26.050 align:middle line:84%
you really don't have
time to write or to paint.

00:42:26.050 --> 00:42:28.120 align:middle line:84%
It's just another
mechanism, it's

00:42:28.120 --> 00:42:29.640 align:middle line:90%
another thing that's going on.

00:42:29.640 --> 00:42:33.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Why do I get the feeling
that making a lot of money,

00:42:33.610 --> 00:42:37.180 align:middle line:84%
to use that phrase, is not as
important to you right now as I

00:42:37.180 --> 00:42:40.540 align:middle line:90%
sit here with you?

00:42:40.540 --> 00:42:43.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Look, the only good thing
about making money is it gives

00:42:43.810 --> 00:42:46.510 align:middle line:84%
you independence,
that's what it does.

00:42:46.510 --> 00:42:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's the best
thing about it.

00:42:49.900 --> 00:42:52.330 align:middle line:90%
This is a red tableau.

00:42:52.330 --> 00:42:58.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's a thanks
to the divine mother

00:42:58.570 --> 00:43:00.380 align:middle line:90%
for saving a child's life.

00:43:00.380 --> 00:43:05.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Ever the independent
spirit, Gloria, now in her 70s,

00:43:05.140 --> 00:43:08.850 align:middle line:84%
is entering a new phase in her
artwork with box sculptures.

00:43:08.850 --> 00:43:12.820 align:middle line:84%
>> What one relates to is
absolutely connected with

00:43:12.820 --> 00:43:17.980 align:middle line:84%
one's childhood because that's
the way the story of it all

00:43:17.980 --> 00:43:19.250 align:middle line:90%
comes together.

00:43:19.250 --> 00:43:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Somewhat abstract, but
always containing kernels

00:43:22.900 --> 00:43:23.960 align:middle line:90%
of the autobiographical.

00:43:23.960 --> 00:43:28.270 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the themes I notice
in a lot of your artwork is

00:43:28.270 --> 00:43:29.216 align:middle line:90%
the divine mother.

00:43:29.216 --> 00:43:30.340 align:middle line:90%
And you speak of her a lot.

00:43:30.340 --> 00:43:30.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:43:30.880 --> 00:43:31.060 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:43:31.060 --> 00:43:32.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Why is that important?

00:43:32.410 --> 00:43:38.725 align:middle line:84%
>> For Gloria, her life is
never far from her work.

00:43:38.725 --> 00:43:44.380 align:middle line:84%
>> The divine mother has more
reality to me than a male

00:43:44.380 --> 00:43:47.070 align:middle line:90%
image, than a male figure.

00:43:47.070 --> 00:43:54.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think also that if you've
always longed for a mother,

00:43:54.610 --> 00:43:58.930 align:middle line:84%
and searched for
a mother, it is as

00:43:58.930 --> 00:44:01.860 align:middle line:84%
if you have a mother,
if you pray to her

00:44:01.860 --> 00:44:05.572 align:middle line:90%
or feel connected to her.

00:44:05.572 --> 00:44:09.940 align:middle line:84%
>> I believe that
there are no endings.

00:44:09.940 --> 00:44:11.440 align:middle line:84%
I believe that there
are beginnings.

00:44:11.440 --> 00:44:12.445 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:44:12.445 --> 00:44:14.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Every day, there's
a new beginning.

00:44:14.290 --> 00:44:17.510 align:middle line:84%
Every day, there's a new
chapter in our lives.

00:44:17.510 --> 00:44:21.790 align:middle line:84%
So I ask you as we
close this conversation,

00:44:21.790 --> 00:44:23.110 align:middle line:90%
what are you beginning?

00:44:23.110 --> 00:44:26.560 align:middle line:84%
What do you begin in this
chapter of your life?

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:29.030 align:middle line:90%
Where are you going?

00:44:29.030 --> 00:44:30.440 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

00:44:30.440 --> 00:44:32.100 align:middle line:90%
What are you beginning?

00:44:32.100 --> 00:44:33.460 align:middle line:90%
>> I have no idea.

00:44:33.460 --> 00:44:34.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Really?

00:44:34.260 --> 00:44:37.732 align:middle line:90%
>> It's going to be a surprise.

00:44:37.732 --> 00:44:40.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't it funny, you
have a preconceived notion,

00:44:40.390 --> 00:44:42.970 align:middle line:84%
I thought you would say,
well, I'm doing this and that.

00:44:42.970 --> 00:44:44.470 align:middle line:84%
And I suppose it's
better in life

00:44:44.470 --> 00:44:47.334 align:middle line:90%
to say, put it in front of me.

00:44:47.334 --> 00:44:48.250 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you mean?

00:44:48.250 --> 00:44:56.740 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I really learned after
Carter's death that you just

00:44:56.740 --> 00:44:58.790 align:middle line:10%
don't know.

00:44:58.790 --> 00:45:00.670 align:middle line:90%
You don't know.

00:45:00.670 --> 00:45:06.670 align:middle line:84%
And you wake up with hope, and
love, and passion in your heart

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:10.166 align:middle line:90%
and hope for the best.

00:45:10.166 --> 00:45:16.000 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, the best compliment
that I think one woman can give

00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:23.200 align:middle line:84%
another woman is not I love your
shoes, I love your lipstick,

00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:25.000 align:middle line:90%
who did your hair?

00:45:25.000 --> 00:45:28.090 align:middle line:84%
I think the best compliment one
woman can give another woman is

00:45:28.090 --> 00:45:31.630 align:middle line:90%
to say, I want to be like you.

00:45:31.630 --> 00:45:34.840 align:middle line:84%
I want to have the
qualities that you have.

00:45:34.840 --> 00:45:35.860 align:middle line:90%
And I say that to you.

00:45:35.860 --> 00:45:38.385 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, Chantal, really, it's--

00:45:38.385 --> 00:45:40.160 align:middle line:90%
>> I do.

00:45:40.160 --> 00:45:41.785 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for this
lovely conversation.

00:45:41.785 --> 00:45:43.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Sweetheart.

00:45:43.110 --> 00:45:44.320 align:middle line:90%
>> You are delightful.

00:45:44.320 --> 00:45:45.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:45:45.300 --> 00:45:47.280 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, sweetheart.

00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:50.630 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

